#import "/formatting.typ": *

= Lemon Pound Cake

#show: recipe.with(sources: <ass_lemon-cake>)[
  #sb[Dry:]
  - 360g all-purpose flour #aside[3 cups]
  - 3g baking soda #aside[1/2 tsp.]
  - 3g salt #aside[1/2 tsp.]
  #LS

  #sb[Wet:]
  - 225g butter #aside[2 sticks]
  - 600g sugar #aside[3 cups] #LS
  - 300g eggs #aside[6 large OR 4 jumbo] #LS
  - 75g lemon juice #aside[1/3 cup]
  - 10g lemon zest, grated #aside[1 1/4 tbsp.] #LS
  - 225g Sour Cream #aside[1 cup]
  #LS

  #sb[Glaze:]
  - 115g powdered sugar #aside[1 cup]
  - 40g lemon juice #aside[3 tbsp.]
]

0. RETRIEVE butter & eggs from refrigeration. Rest until room temperature #pause[\~1-2
    hours]
+ PREHEAT oven, 180°C #aside[350°F]
+ SIFT dry ingredients into medium bowl.
+ MIX wet ingredients separately, medium speed:
  + Butter & sugar, 8-10 minutes.
  + Eggs, one at a time, until combined.
  + Lemon juice & lemon zest, until combined.
+ SWAP mixer attachment for Dutch hook.
+ MIX into wet ingredients, low speed:
  + Dry ingredients.
  + Sour cream.
+ GREASE two 9"×5" loaf pans.#footnote[The original recipe suggests a single, 10-12 cup
    Bundt pan may work better.]
+ POUR batter into loaf pans.
+ BAKE covered, until knife tests clean. #pause[\~1 hour]
+ COOL cake in loaf pan. #pause[\~15 min.]
+ TRANSFER cake to flat surface.
+ COAT with glaze.
+ COVER airtight, and possibly refrigerate or freeze#footnote[~It should be possible to
    freeze this cake for up to 3 months.], until ready to serve.
